  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nThe background service on Android, which is required to get notifications on new messages, always stops after a few hours.\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\nSee above\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nBackground service should keep running until I stop it\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nRuns for a few hours then just stops.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) Open Status\r\n2) Turn on notifications\r\n3) See Background service for notifications appear in Android notification list\r\n4) After a few hours to 1-2 days it just disappears/\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: 1.16.0 (20210827115911) \r\n- Operating System: Android (Samsung)\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
