    "body": "Hello @dankrad\r\nSorry it took so long to give an update on this issue.\r\n\r\nI've reproduced it on my Huawei device, and apparently, the reason is indeed in the power-saving mode. \r\nIf enable it on the device, enable the push notification service and send the Status app to the background, it will log out after ~ 30 minutes. The notification service will be displayed as enabled but in fact, it will stop working. \r\nAfter reopening the app and logging in, the notification will restart. \r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce:**\r\n1. Enable the power-saving mode on an Android device\r\n2. Open Status and enable push notifications\r\n3. Send the app to the background\r\n4. Reopen the app in ~ 30 min\r\n\r\n[Status.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/7339510/Status.log)\r\n[geth.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/7339509/geth.log)\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/137172592-3f41bd9b-97b3-4991-be0e-20da8ae05ec9.mp4\r\n\r\nProbably, this behavior is expected with the power-saving mode enabled. But better to ask @cammellos  for clarification.\r\nTake a look, please, when you have time. Thank you!\r\n",
